I used HackerRank, which allowed me to practice basic coding skills. I practiced by solving a beginner-level coding problem using HackerRank. This helped me understand logical thinking and problem-solving, which is an essential skill for programming. This is a good place to begin, especially since HackerRank offers coding problems for people who are new to coding.

For the second part, I used Google Forms to create a “Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz” with five questions, including both multiple-choice and short answer questions. This allowed me to understand how to create surveys using Google Forms.

I find that both tools are extremely helpful from an academic perspective. The coding tools will allow me to improve my coding skills, while Google Forms can be used for quizzes, feedback, or group activities. Overall, the task has allowed me to understand both technical practice and digital tools.
